<div class='bookAuthorProfile__about'>

<span id="freeTextContainer2704137432008576985"><b>Rick Bayless</b> has written six cookbooks, including <i>Mexican Everyday</i> and <i>Fiesta at Rick&apos;s</i>. His product line of prepared foods is sold coast to coast. With his wife Deann he owns and operates Chicago’s casual Frontera Grill, named “Outstanding Restaurant” by the James Beard Foundation, and the four-star fine-dining Topolobampo. XOCO, a Leed-certified quick-serve restaurant, opened in 2009. He is the </span>
  <span id="freeText2704137432008576985" style="display:none"><b>Rick Bayless</b> has written six cookbooks, including <i>Mexican Everyday</i> and <i>Fiesta at Rick's</i>. His product line of prepared foods is sold coast to coast. With his wife Deann he owns and operates Chicago’s casual Frontera Grill, named “Outstanding Restaurant” by the James Beard Foundation, and the four-star fine-dining Topolobampo. XOCO, a Leed-certified quick-serve restaurant, opened in 2009. He is the host of the public television series <i>Mexico—One Plate at a Time</i>.</span>
